{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{SERVER_NAME}}": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "@your-package/mcp-server"
      ],
      "env": {
        "API_KEY": "${{{API_KEY_VAR}}}"
      }
    }
  }
}

<!--
NOTE: Claude Code .mcp.json does NOT support HTTP/SSE transports with 'url' or 'httpUrl' fields.
All MCP servers must use stdio transport with 'command' and 'args'.

If you have an HTTP-based MCP server, you need to:
1. Create a wrapper script that runs the server
2. Use 'command' to execute the wrapper
3. The server communicates via stdio, not HTTP

Invalid formats (will cause errors):
- { "url": "http://..." }          ❌
- { "httpUrl": "https://..." }     ❌
- { "type": "http", "url": "..." } ❌

Valid format (stdio only):
- { "command": "node", "args": ["server.js"] } ✅
-->
